    <string name="audio_transport_mini_example">PRAISE THE OMNISSIAH</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_2">In imo campanilis machina sigillata murmurare incipit</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_3">Lucerna septima ardet, sed porta remota silet</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_4">Ultra portum cineris navis peregrina aquam nigram transit</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_5">Cum campanae ferreae respondent, sera exterior adhuc tenet</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_long_1">Tabularium campanilis memorat fornacem orientalem ante auroram respondisse, multo antequam lucernae tecti surgere deberent. Tres ministri rotas aeneas manu verterunt, dum fuligo ex foraminibus superioribus defluebat et super gradus subsidet. Post operculum sigillatum murmur grave atque constans exortum est, tam diu tractum ut scribae nocturni modum eius in tabulis ceratis pulsare inciperent. Cum nota ultima tenuata est, nemo pessulum ferreum tetigit, et tamen omnes testes eandem lineam subscripserunt: machina infra sponte sua experrecta erat.</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_long_2">Secunda vigilia lucernae portae compositae sunt, serae exteriores iterum temptatae sunt, et fuligo de cardinibus catenarum rasa est. Nullum signum e transitu remoto venit, sed pavimentum lapideum intervallis brevibus contremiscebat, quasi gravis tractus sub aula laborem imperfectum repetisset. Custodes omnem motum ad clepsydram numeraverunt et invenerunt figuram redire, quotiens murus occidentalis totum pondus venti suscipiebat. Antequam vigilia dimitteretur, cera recens super seram interiorem pressa est, et relatio hoc monito clausa est: silentium ultra portam nunc silentium occupatum erat.</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_long_3">Chronica fornacis referunt lucernas rubras singillatim elevatas esse, donec tota camera quasi prunae sub fumo congestae reluceret. Cum catena ultima stetit, scribae signorum omnem pulsum in tabulas ceratas rettulerunt, dum porticus superiores stridore hamorum ferreorum respondebant. Quattuor responsa lenta per trabes redierunt, unumquoque priore infirmius, nec tamen ulli registratores convenire potuerunt quae paries vocem tulisset. Linea extrema notat campanas usque ad auroram intentas non esse revinctas, quia nemo in camera audire volebat quid quinto vocatui responderet.</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_thematic_long_4">Relatio navigationis e litore cineris narrat transitum nocturnum sub luna fracta et caelo pulvere fornacis obscurato. Lucernae carinae velatae erant, conclave chartarum silebat, et solus lentus pulsus sacrarii machinae horas sub tabulato notabat. Prope mediam noctem gubernator iussit proram tribus gradibus flecti, postquam formae pallidae inter fluctus nigros moveri visae sunt, quamquam nullus sonus ad marginem navis pervenit. Mane navis lumina portus iterum repperit, et nota finalis dicit omnes lucernas gratiarum causa recreatas esse praeter eam quae iuxta cistam sigillatam stabat.</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_2">SEAL THE OUTER LOCK</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_3">COPPER WARDENS STIR THE DRIVE</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_4">SEVENTH LAMP LIT GATE STILL SILENT</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_5">HOLD FORMATION BELOW IRON MASTS</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_long_1">BELL TOWER LEDGER. EAST FURNACE ANSWERED BEFORE DAWN. THREE ATTENDANTS TURNED THE BRASS WHEELS BY HAND WHILE SOOT FELL THROUGH THE UPPER VENTS. A LOW STEADY HUM CAME THROUGH THE SEALED HATCH. FINAL LINE STATES THE MACHINE BELOW WOKE OF ITS OWN ACCORD.</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_long_2">SECOND WATCH REPORT. GATEHOUSE LAMPS TRIMMED, OUTER BOLTS TESTED AGAIN, CHAIN HINGES SCRAPED CLEAN. NO SIGNAL CAME FROM THE FAR CORRIDOR, BUT THE FLOOR KEPT SHAKING IN SHORT INTERVALS ABOVE THE DRIVE HALL. FRESH WAX WAS PRESSED OVER THE INNER LOCK BEFORE DISMISSAL.</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_long_3">FURNACE CHRONICLE. RED LAMPS RAISED ONE BY ONE UNTIL THE CHAMBER GLOWED THROUGH THE SMOKE. SIGNAL CLERKS COPIED EACH PULSE INTO WAX TABLETS WHILE IRON HOOKS SCRAPED IN THE UPPER GALLERIES. FOUR SLOW RETURNS CAME BACK. BELLS LEFT UNWOUND UNTIL DAWN.</string>
    <string name="audio_sample_pro_long_4">ASH COAST VOYAGE. HULL LAMPS HOODED, CHART ROOM SILENT, ENGINE SANCTUM MARKING THE HOURS BELOW DECK. PROW TURNED THREE DEGREES AFTER PALE SHAPES MOVED BETWEEN THE BLACK SWELLS. HARBOR LIGHTS RETURNED AT DAWN. ONE LAMP BESIDE THE SEALED COFFER STAYED DARK.</string>
